<div class="body" id="fhbody-173570642">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-173570642" class="p">
			
		 	
				Google said on Thursday it had <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/google-terminates-28-employees-protest-israeli-cloud-contract-2024-04-18/">terminated 28 employees</a> after some staff participated in protests against the company's cloud contract with the Israeli government. From a report:<i> The Alphabet unit said a small number of protesting employees entered and disrupted work at a few unspecified office locations. "Physically impeding other employees' work and preventing them from accessing our facilities is a clear violation of our policies, and completely unacceptable behavior," the company said in a statement.<br> <br>

Google said it had concluded individual investigations, resulting in the termination of 28 employees, and would continue to investigate and take action as needed. In a statement on Medium, Google workers affiliated with the No Tech for Apartheid campaign called it a "flagrant act of retaliation" and said that some employees who did not directly participate in Tuesday's protests were also among those Google fired.</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
